<font color="#FF0000">NO CLOSURE</font><br>
<tt>Fri May  9  3:53:10 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Time goes by, and still there has not been final word on 400 or so POWs that there was either photographic or eyewitness evidence that they were in custody.  I don't expect an accounting down to the last body.  That would be impossible for a number of reasons.  But I find no excuse for not coming up with a man or remains or at least records of all those known to have been held.
<p><code>-- gerald_ney@icpphil.navy.mil  (Geradl Ney, &quot;professor&quot;, 7/68-7/69) </code><p>


